---
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<aside class="author-bio">
  <div class="author-avatar" aria-hidden="true">IP</div>
  <div class="author-text">
    <p class="author-name">Written by {SITE.author}</p>
    <p class="author-role">Privacy advocate, training for a career in cybersecurity</p>
    <p class="bio">
      I got into this the hard way: after being scammed, I started studying for a career in
      cybersecurity and built Stay Safe Guide as I went. My rule is simple. Trust is earned,
      never assumed, and even a company you trust today can change hands tomorrow while the
      data you handed over lives on. I hold CompTIA Security+ and Microsoft SC-900, with
      SC-200 next, and I test what I write in my own home lab. Privacy isn't about having
      something to hide. It's about not handing over more than you need.
    </p>
  </div>
</aside>
